definitions.definition: A flower , cat etc., that has two colours.
A flag with such colours, consisting of two stripes that are either vertical or horizontal .
examples: The national flags of Algeria , Bahrain , Indonesia , Malta , Monaco , Poland , Portugal , Ukraine and the Vatican City are all bicolours .

main_definition: ( British spelling ) A flower , cat etc., that has two colours.
secondary_definitions: ( British spelling ) A flag with such colours, consisting of two stripes that are either vertical or horizontal .
